                    <span>The problems in this book were arranged the way  that leads readers understand simple concepts  first, then bring you to problems and applications.  In addtion, my professor Dr. Mott (he wrote one of the top  selling discrete book) recommanded  this book to me as well. I found it  VERY helpful. <p>Yes, I think it servers as an aid to textbooks. You cannot  teach yourself discrete math by reading it.<p>By the way, it doesn't have  alot Hamiltionian  cycle examples in there.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Critics aside, this is really a good book</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
